              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USATAM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using K150",
                "cyclotron at the Cyclotron Institute at Texas A&M",
                "University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Active volume of the TPC. Target was methane gas CH4",
                "with purity of 99.999%. Pressure in TPC was adjusted",
                "to stop incoming 8Be beam before the last 16 rows of",
                "the central pads to 435 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A time projection chamber (TPC) TexAT was used for",
                "identification and tracking of reaction products.",
                "TexAT has a planar geometry with Micromegas readout.",
                "Micromegas detector has active area 224 x 224 mm2.",
                "TPC allowed for complete kinematic reconstruction",
                "of each event"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chamber is integral part of",
                "TexAT, located close to the entrance window.",
                "Ionization chamber is used for beam particle",
                "identification and overal normalization."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Total nine Si-CsI(Tl) telescope",
                "detectors were positioned in the forward region of",
                "TexAT chamber. Si detectors with area 5cm x 5cm,",
                "700-1000 mu-m thick were divided into four 2.5cm x",
                "2.5cm square segments. Each Si detector was backed by",
                "5cm x 5cm x 4cm CsI(Tl) scintillation detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 8B beam was produced in the reaction",
                "6Li(3He,n)8B. The primary 6Li beam made above",
                "reaction in a liquid nitrogen cooled 3He gas cell.",
                "Cell was 9.2 cm long with diameter of 19 mm and has 4",
                "mu-m thick Havar entrance and exit windows. Pressure",
                "of 3He gas was 810 torr. The energy of the primary",
                "6Li beam was 13.2MeV/A, resulting 8B beam has energy",
                " (60.8+- 1.2) MeV and intensity about 10E+3 pps."
              ]
            }
          ],
